# SQL JOIN Syntax Table

|JOIN Type|SQL Syntax|Description|
|---|---|---|
|**INNER JOIN**|`SELECT A.column1, B.column2 FROM TableA A INNER JOIN TableB B ON A.key = B.key;`|Returns rows where keys match in both tables (A ∩ B).|
|**LEFT JOIN**|`SELECT A.column1, B.column2 FROM TableA A LEFT JOIN TableB B ON A.key = B.key;`|Returns all rows from TableA, with matching rows from TableB; NULL if no match.|
|**RIGHT JOIN**|`SELECT A.column1, B.column2 FROM TableA A RIGHT JOIN TableB B ON A.key = B.key;`|Returns all rows from TableB, with matching rows from TableA; NULL if no match.|
|**FULL OUTER JOIN**|`SELECT A.column1, B.column2 FROM TableA A FULL OUTER JOIN TableB B ON A.key = B.key;`|Returns all rows from both tables; NULL where no match exists.|

