| Fetch Syntax                          | Description                                                 | Example                                                                        |
| ------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| FETCH FIRST n ROWS ONLY               | Limit results set to first n rows (SQL standard)            | `SELECT * FROM employees FETCH FIRST 10 ROWS ONLY`                             |
| FETCH NEXT n ROWS ONLY                | Limit results set to next n rows (used with offset)         | `SELECT * FROM employees OFFSET 5 ROWS FETCH NEXT 10 ROWS ONLY`                |
| OFFSET n ROWS FETCH FIRST m ROWS ONLY | Skips n rows, then returns m rows                           | `SELECT * FROM products ORDER BY price OFFSET 20 ROWS FETCH FIRST 5 ROWS ONLY` |
| FETCH ABSOLUTE n                      | Positions cursor at specific row number (with cursors)      | `FETCH ABSOLUTE 15 FROM my_cursor`                                             |
| FETCH RELATIVE n                      | Moves cursor n positions relative to current (with cursors) | `FETCH RELATIVE 3 FROM my_cursor`                                              |
| FETCH FIRST                           | Moves cursor to first row (with cursors)                    | `FETCH FIRST FROM my_cursor`                                                   |
