SET OPERATORS
Combine the results of multiple queries into a single results set

Types:
- Union
- Union All
- Except (minus)
- Intersect

Rules
#1 Set operators can be used almost in all clauses
	WHERE | JOIN | GROUP BY | HAVING
	only ORDER BY only once and at the end of the query
#2 The numbers of columns must be the same  in each query
#3 Data Types of COlumns in each query must be compatible "same data types"
#4 The order of columns must be the same
#5 The column names in the result set are determined by the column names specified in the first query.
#6 Even if all rules are met and SQL shows no errors the result may be incorrect
	Incorrect column selection leads to inaccurate results.


Syntax
```SQL

SELECT FirstName, LastName FROM customers
UNION
SELECT FirstName, LastName FROM employees
```
