### UNION
returns all distrinct rows from both query.

Removes duplicates rows from the results.
Orders does not matter just keep in mind the naming of the column are given from the first script

```SQL
Combine the data from employees and customers into one table
SELECT customerid, firstname, lastname
FROM Sales.Customers
UNION
SELECT employeeid, firstname,lastname
FROM Sales.Employees ORDER BY customerid;
```


### UNION ALL
returns all rows from both query, including duplicates

Differences between Union and Union ALL
- Union ALL is generally faster than Union because it doesn't have to check for duplicates
```SQL
Combine the data from employees and customers into one table with duplicates
SELECT customerid, firstname, lastname
FROM Sales.Customers
UNION ALL
SELECT employeeid, firstname,lastname
FROM Sales.Employees ORDER BY customerid;
```


